.TH shell 1 "April 15, 2020" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B  The shell is executed by typing ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
A shell is a command language interpreter that executes commands read from the
standard input or from a file. Our shell does not support the arguments passed
to it.
.br
shell is a program that provides the traditional, text-only user interface for
Linux and other Unix-like operating systems.
.SH OVERVIEW
Reading from either the terminal or files, simple_shell interprets and executes
commands.
.SH EXECUTABLES
.br
- Executes any command with its arguments
.br
- Executes built-in commands
.br
- Handle the command seperator ;
.br
- Handle && and ||
.br
- handle the $? variables
.br
- handle the $$ variables
.SH BUILT-IN FUNCTIONS
.br
 - exit : exit the shell
.br
 - cd : The cd (change directory) command is used to change the current working
directory in Linux and other Unix-like operating systems.
.br
 - env : Display the environment variables
.SH EXAMPLE
.br
 $ ./hsh
.br
 #:)$ /bin/ls
.br
 hsh main.c shell.c
.br
 #:)$ exit
.br
 $
.br
 hsh main.c shell.c
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
